article.headline: No. 9 Stanford holds LIU to 28 points in opening win
article.linkText: No. 9 Stanford holds LIU to 28 points in opening win
article.story:
MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Brooke Smith had 15 points and six rebounds
to lead Stanford (No. 9 ESPN/USA Today; No. 13 AP) to a 69-28 season-opening victory Saturday
over Long Island University in the semifinals of the Subway Classic
tournament.

Candice Wiggins added 14 points and six rebounds for Stanford.

"This is a really inexperienced team," Stanford coach Tara
VanDerveer said. "We played a lot of people, just trying to give
them a taste of what it's like on court. Our bench is going to need
to play well for us."

Sara Oblak led the Blackbirds with 10 points and nine rebounds.
LIU shot a dismal 4-of-31 in the second half.

The Cardinal jumped to a 22-2 lead with only 7 minutes gone in
the first half. Stanford coach Tara VanDerveer soon rested her
starters, with no Cardinal player logging more than 23 minutes.

Stanford's defense produced 10 steals and 10 blocks. The
Cardinals ran the fast break after nearly every rebound or steal in
the first half en route to a 40-17 halftime lead.

The Cardinal plays Sunday afternoon against Minnesota (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today; No. 16 AP),
which beat San Francisco 80-62.
